  "texts": [
    "Unless otherwise stated, all statistical hypothesis testing was conducted with permutation tests, which do not assume any parametric form of the underlying probability distributions of the sample.",
    "All tests were two-sided and non-paired, unless otherwise noted.",
    "Each test was performed with 1,000 runs, where P < 0.001 indicates the highest significance achievable given the number of runs performed.",
    "When comparing changes in behaviour due to genetic silencing versus control flies (Fig. 1e), we accounted for multiple hypothesis testing by correcting the false discovery rate with the Benjamini-Hochberg procedure with α = 0.05.",
    "Paired permutation tests were performed when comparing prediction performance between models (Fig. 2e) for which paired samples were randomly permuted with one another."
